    <element name="Dragonblade" type="Class" source="Tanares RPG 5e" id="ID_TRPG_CLASS_DRAGONBLADE">
        <description>
            <p>Masters of draconic power and strategic thinking, these skilled combatants protect Tanares from penumbral cultists and creatures, serving as defenders, monster hunters, and military leaders for the Draconic Council.</p>
            <h4>Dragonblade</h4>
            <p>The dragonblades are elite combatants with a unique fighting
style, harnessing the ancient and mystic powers of dragons.
Most of these skilled warriors serve the Draconic Council
and take on various roles, such as diplomats, gladiators,
and monster hunters, fighting against the corruptive
forces that threaten the world.</p>
<p class="indent">Each dragonblade follows a Draconic Soul path, symbolized by a dragon color that bestows upon them elemental
powers associated with that dragon. These elemental forces
augment their martial prowess, enabling them to combat
the sinister otherworldly forces threatening their world.
Their cunning also allows them to serve as battle strategists, outwitting enemies and controlling the battlefield with
strategic prowess.</p>
<p class="indent">As the Malrokian Curse looms over Tanares, threatening
to unleash chaos and devastation should large-scale battles
erupt, dragonblades are required to avert such conflicts and
hunt the cultists and aberrations that strive to cause them.
Their missions demand extraordinary courage, tactical expertise, and unwavering dedication to the cause.</p>
<p class="indent">In their quest, dragonblades often face formidable adversaries such as the Cult of Shadow Wing, which seeks to
corrupt all creatures, including dragons, turning them into
penumbral creatures that empower the eldritch Ungods</p>
<p class="indent">As the dragonblades grapple with their daunting tasks,
the enigmatic Draconic Council is beset with internal strife,
casting shadows over the future of Tanares. The Council’s
divisions stem from contrasting beliefs regarding the potential of mortals. The majestic Gold Avatar Dragon, Isendden,
champions a faction that fervently trusts in mortal potential
and destiny. In stark contrast, the formidable Black Avatar
Dragon, Zaldrus, spearheads a faction that perceives mortals
as feeble and susceptible to corruption. As this clandestine
struggle for dominion over the council unfolds, whispers of
political intrigue echoes in the Draconic Towers</p>
<p class="indent">Undeterred by these challenges, the dragonblades persevere
in their mission. They venture into the Penumbral Plane to
free captured dragons, dismantle the Shadow Wing’s plans,
and vanquish their foes. As the embodiment of strategic
combat against the encroaching darkness, the dragonblades
unleash their intellect, martial skill, and the awe-inspiring
power of dragons to vanquish their foes.</p>
            
       
            <h4>CREATING A DRAGONBLADE</h4>
            <p>The first step in creating your dragonblade character is to
determine whether or not they are affiliated with the Draconic
Council. Most dragonblades serve the Council, but there
are many wandering dragonblades who could have served
as the character’s mentor.</p>
            <p class="indent">If they are affiliated with the Council, work with your
Game Master to determine its ranking, who trained it and
who is currently its superior, as well as the philosophy and
goals of its group inside the Council.</p>
            <p class="indent">If they are not affiliated with the Council, work with your
Game Master to determine the character’s mentor, the mentor’s history, and why they trained the character.</p>
            <p class="indent">Finally, decide what led your character to a life of adventure. Were they fulfilling a mission given to them by the
Council? Did their studies make them question some of the
things taught to them by their master or the Council? Did
they encounter a group in need of their leadership that could
help them achieve their personal goals? Did they embark on
their adventure as part of their training?</p>
           
            <h2>CLASS FEATURES</h2>
            <p>As an dragonblade, you gain the following class features.</p>
            <h5 class="caption">HIT POINTS</h5>
            <ul class="unstyled">
                <li><strong>Hit Dice:</strong> 1d8 per dragonblade level</li>
                <li><strong>Hit Points at 1st Level:</strong> 8 + your Constitution modifier</li>
                <li><strong>Hit Points at Higher Levels:</strong> 1d8 (or 5) + your Constitution modifier per dragonblade level after 1st</li>
            </ul>
            <h5 class="caption">PROFICIENCIES</h5>
            <ul class="unstyled mb">
                <li><strong>Armor:</strong> All armor, shields</li>
                <li><strong>Weapons:</strong> simple weapons, martial weapons</li>
                <li><strong>Tools:</strong> blacksmith tools or cartographer tools</li>
            </ul>
            <ul class="unstyled">
                <li><strong>Saving Throws:</strong> Intelligence, Constitution</li>
                <li><strong>Skills:</strong> Choose two skills from Arcana, History, Investigation, Nature, Perception, and Religion</li>
            </ul>
            <h5 class="caption">EQUIPMENT</h5>
            <p>You start with the following equipment, in addition to the equipment granted by your background:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>(a) one-handed martial weapon and a shield or (b) two-handed martial weapon</li>
                <li>(a) chain mail or (b) chain shirt, longbow and 20 arrows</li>
                <li>(a) a scholar’s pack or (b) an explorer’s pack</li>
                
            </ul>

