    <element name="Claws and Scales" type="Class Feature" source="Tanares RPG 5e" id="ID_TRPG_CLASS_FEATURE_DRAGONBLADE_CLAWS_AND_SCALES">
        <description>
            <p>At 1st level, your mastery allows the draconic energy to
channel into your armor and weapon, turning them as innate
to you as scales and claws are to a dragon. When you attack
with melee or ranged weapons, you can use your Intelligence
modifier, instead of Strength or Dexterity, for the attack and
damage rolls. Additionally, ignore the Strength requirement
for wearing armor, and only consider half of its weight towards your carrying capacity</p>
        </description>
        <sheet>
            <description>When attacking with melee or ranged weapons you can use you Intelligence Modifier instead of Strength or Dexterity for the attack and damge rolls. Ignore the Strength requirement for wearing armor and you armor weight is halved. NOTE: FINESSE WEAPONS CALCULATIONS ARE BROKEN.</description>
        </sheet>
        <rules>
        <!-- removes the ability bonuses for melee and ranged so i can add INT modifier-->
            <stat name="ranged:attack" value="-dexterity:modifier" />
			<stat name="melee:attack" value="-strength:modifier"  />
			<stat name="ranged:damage" value="-dexterity:modifier"  />
			<stat name="melee:damage" value="-strength:modifier" />

<!-- trying to fix finesse weapons here. Finesse weapons dont get the negative dex mod from above
            <stat name="melee:attack" value="-dexterity:modifier"  requirements="finesse"/>
            <stat name="melee:damage" value="-dexterity:modifier"  requirements="ID_INTERNAL_WEAPON_PROPERTY_FINESSE"/>
 -->
            <stat name="ranged:attack" value="intelligence:modifier" />
			<stat name="melee:attack" value="intelligence:modifier"  />
			<stat name="ranged:damage" value="intelligence:modifier"  />
			<stat name="melee:damage" value="intelligence:modifier"  />
        </rules>
